caption:
Table 1. Comparisons on the DAVIS 2016 and DAVIS 2017 validation set where ground 
truths are available. 'OL' indicates the use of online-learning strategy. The best results 
are bold-faced, and the second best results are underlined.

Table 2. Comparisons on the DAVIS 2017 test-dev and Youtube-VOS 2018 validation 
sets where ground truths are unavailable. 'OL' indicates the use of online-learning 
strategy. The best results are bold-faced, and the second best results are underlined.

Table 3. Ablation study of our proposed methods. 'HaS' and 'KM' indicate the use of 
Hide-and-Seek pre-training and kernelized memory read operation, respectively. Note 
that we did not use additional VOS training data for the ablation study. Only either 
DAVIS or Youtube-VOS is used, depending on the target evaluation benchmark.
